\f0\b Understanding the importance of ReAct:\
- 
\f1\b0 ReAct overcomes common issues involving hallucination and error propagation \'97> when it comes to chain-of-thought style reasoning.\
- The tight synergy between Acting and Reasoning allows humans to quickly understand tasks \'97> proper utilization of the tools that it has been provided.\
\'97> What differentiates Chain-of-Thought vs ReAct is that Chain-of-Thought consists of reasoning only, without any kind of actions present.\
\'97> also, we want to avoid veering to the side of Action only, meaning independently working in terms of Action or Reasoning in isolation isn\'92t ideal \'97> ReAct is the paradigm that combines both Reasoning and Action.\
- The process is broken down into 3 steps \'97> Think, Act and Observe (environment of the model is what enables observation).\
\

\f0\b Breakdown of 4 types of prompting methods present: (think of them as 4 paradigms present)\
1. 
\f1\b0 standard \'97> This is what traditional Generative AI models do \'97> token based prediction enabled via transformer architecture.\
2. Chain-of-thought \'97> Consists of reason only \'97> Also not ideal in this case.\
3. Act-only \'97> Provides output solely based on actions, without thinking and observing (similar to how soldiers are trained in real world, to just follow orders without questioning anything)\
4. ReAct (reason + act) \'97> This is true intelligence, before taking action, assessing whether that particular action needs to be taken.\
