\fs48 ITFormer Notes Breakdown:\

\fs36 What IT Former stands for (acronym wise):\

\f1\b0\fs24 - ITFormer = instruct Time Transformer\
- New framework, that combines time series encoders with frozen LLMs.\
	- but this raises 2 questions \'97> what is time series encoders and what is frozen LLMs?\
- The purpose of time series encoders is to convert time-ordered data into machine readable format \'97> This leads to the question: what is the relationship between time series data and time ordered data? Rather, what is the relation between the two?\
		- Time series data is a specialized subset of time-ordered data. The key differentiator between time series data and time ordered data is that time series data, the order of the data points matter \'97> due to drawing analysis/correlation between such data points in different times.\
			- This correlation, used interchageably as \'93autocorrelation\'94, represents a form of statistical relationship of a variable with it\'92s past values.\
		- On the other hand, a frozen LLM are LLMs trained on a set of frozen parameters with the intention of keeping knowledge intact, prevent model degradation that typically occurs over time under natural constraints.\
		- When it comes to being used together, time series encoders are used to prepare frozen data in order to ensure it works together with frozen LLM \'97> allows for specific finetuned LLM to make generalizations and enhanced reasoning specialized for forecasting and question answering format, without need for extensive retraining.}